  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Samuel Joseph May is &quot;rejoiced to see that old Massachusetts is not quite asleep on the subject of Texas.&quot; He offers Maria Weston Chapman a copy of &quot;a report of the speech I made last Jan&apos;y at the Anti-Texas Convention.&quot; He gave a copy of this report to the [Anti-Slavery?] Reporter for publication, but it was suppressed. Maria W. Chapman may publish it in the Liberty Bell or elsewhere. [The Liberty Bell for 1846 contains the &quot;Extract from a speech at the Anti-Texan meeting in Faneuil Hall, 1845,&quot; by Samuel Joseph May, p. 73-76.]</subfield>
